<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="118" pageId="7" pageNumber="116" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,334,265,291]" box="[189,334,265,291]" pageId="7" pageNumber="116">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,334,265,291]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="116" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,334,265,291]" pageId="7" pageNumber="116">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1399,323,419]" pageId="7" pageNumber="116">
BODY. 
<typeStatus box="[274,383,323,349]" pageId="7" pageNumber="116">Holotype</typeStatus>
complete (ECOSUR-303), integument slightly eroded. Body light brown, 
<quantity box="[1311,1399,323,349]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="116" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[256,346,358,385]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="116" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
wide, fourth parathoracic segments, 12 abdominal segments, caudal peduncle 
<quantity box="[1271,1339,358,385]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="116" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
long (
<figureCitation box="[198,269,393,419]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1852,1878]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,472,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-45@7.[189,1398,472,1815]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Mariansabellaria caribbea sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-303). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view.B. Anterior region left lateral view.C. Anterior region ventral view.D. Nuchal spines.E. Parathorax left lateral view. F. Caudal peduncle. Abbreviations: bo = building organ; c1 = cirrus 1st thoracic; c2 = cirri 2nd thoracic segment; ne = parathoracic neuropodium; no = parathoracic notopodium. Numbers indicate the tentacular filaments. Scale bars: A–B, E: 1 mm; C, F: 0.5 mm; D: 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885282" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885282/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="116">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885282" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6885282" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885282/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="116" startId="7.[189,232,1852,1878]" targetBox="[189,1398,472,1814]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[187,1399,1852,2020]" pageId="7" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,269,1852,1878]" pageId="7" pageNumber="116">Fig. 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Chávez-López, 2022" authorityName="Chávez-López" authorityYear="2022" box="[279,600,1852,1878]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="7" pageNumber="116" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="caribbea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[279,600,1852,1878]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="116">Mariansabellaria caribbea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[610,705,1853,1879]" pageId="7" pageNumber="116" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype (ECOSUR-303). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1040,1059,1852,1878]" pageId="7" pageNumber="116">A</emphasis>
. Complete specimen, dorsal view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[256,276,1888,1914]" pageId="7" pageNumber="116">B</emphasis>
. Anterior region left lateral view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[658,679,1887,1913]" pageId="7" pageNumber="116">C</emphasis>
. Anterior region ventral view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1028,1049,1888,1914]" pageId="7" pageNumber="116">D</emphasis>
. Nuchal spines. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1237,1257,1888,1914]" pageId="7" pageNumber="116">E</emphasis>
. Parathorax left lateral view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[389,406,1923,1949]" pageId="7" pageNumber="116">F</emphasis>
. Caudal peduncle. Abbreviations: bo = building organ; c1 = cirrus 1 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1216,1227,1922,1936]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="116">st</superScript>
thoracic; c2 = cirri 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[263,280,1957,1971]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="116">nd</superScript>
thoracic segment; ne = parathoracic neuropodium; no = parathoracic notopodium. Numbers indicate the tentacular filaments. Scale bars: A–B, E: 1 mm; C, F: 0.5 mm; D: 200 µm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="8.[188,1400,265,397]" lastBlockId="9.[189,1400,265,467]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="118" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">
OPERCULUM. Opercular disc truncates, two rows of translucent, amber paleae: outer row with 54–56 paleae on each lobe, inner row with 4–5 paleae on each lobe (
<figureCitation box="[895,1020,300,326]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1852,1878]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,472,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-45@7.[189,1398,472,1815]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Mariansabellaria caribbea sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-303). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view.B. Anterior region left lateral view.C. Anterior region ventral view.D. Nuchal spines.E. Parathorax left lateral view. F. Caudal peduncle. Abbreviations: bo = building organ; c1 = cirrus 1st thoracic; c2 = cirri 2nd thoracic segment; ne = parathoracic neuropodium; no = parathoracic notopodium. Numbers indicate the tentacular filaments. Scale bars: A–B, E: 1 mm; C, F: 0.5 mm; D: 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885282" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885282/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">Fig. 3A, C</figureCitation>
). Outer paleae cylindrical, 
<quantity box="[1332,1399,300,327]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="117" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
long (
<figureCitation box="[257,353,335,361]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,445,1784]" captionTargetId="figure-77@8.[192,1396,445,1784]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Mariansabellaria caribbea sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-303). A. Outer palea dorsal. B. Basal region of dorsal outer palea. C. Middle region of dorsal outer palea. D. Details of the outer palea tip. E. Basal region of ventral outer palea. F. Dorsal inner palea. G. Ventral inner palea. H. Details of the inner palea tip.I. Parathoracic chaeta. J–K. Abdominal chaetae.L. Abdominal uncini. Numbers indicate the rows of teeth. Scale bars: A = 200 µm; B, D, H–I, K = 20 µm; C, L = 10 µm; E = 50 µm; F–G, J = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885284/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Proximal region with compact thecae partially surrounding the blade, margins slightly expanded, denticulate (
<figureCitation box="[463,590,370,397]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,445,1784]" captionTargetId="figure-77@8.[192,1396,445,1784]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Mariansabellaria caribbea sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-303). A. Outer palea dorsal. B. Basal region of dorsal outer palea. C. Middle region of dorsal outer palea. D. Details of the outer palea tip. E. Basal region of ventral outer palea. F. Dorsal inner palea. G. Ventral inner palea. H. Details of the inner palea tip.I. Parathoracic chaeta. J–K. Abdominal chaetae.L. Abdominal uncini. Numbers indicate the rows of teeth. Scale bars: A = 200 µm; B, D, H–I, K = 20 µm; C, L = 10 µm; E = 50 µm; F–G, J = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885284/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">Fig. 4B, E</figureCitation>
). Middle region with thecae partially surrounding the blade, margins expanded, pectinate (
<figureCitation box="[446,544,265,291]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,445,1784]" captionTargetId="figure-77@8.[192,1396,445,1784]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Mariansabellaria caribbea sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-303). A. Outer palea dorsal. B. Basal region of dorsal outer palea. C. Middle region of dorsal outer palea. D. Details of the outer palea tip. E. Basal region of ventral outer palea. F. Dorsal inner palea. G. Ventral inner palea. H. Details of the inner palea tip.I. Parathoracic chaeta. J–K. Abdominal chaetae.L. Abdominal uncini. Numbers indicate the rows of teeth. Scale bars: A = 200 µm; B, D, H–I, K = 20 µm; C, L = 10 µm; E = 50 µm; F–G, J = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885284/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). Tip pinnate (
<figureCitation box="[725,825,265,291]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,445,1784]" captionTargetId="figure-77@8.[192,1396,445,1784]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Mariansabellaria caribbea sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-303). A. Outer palea dorsal. B. Basal region of dorsal outer palea. C. Middle region of dorsal outer palea. D. Details of the outer palea tip. E. Basal region of ventral outer palea. F. Dorsal inner palea. G. Ventral inner palea. H. Details of the inner palea tip.I. Parathoracic chaeta. J–K. Abdominal chaetae.L. Abdominal uncini. Numbers indicate the rows of teeth. Scale bars: A = 200 µm; B, D, H–I, K = 20 µm; C, L = 10 µm; E = 50 µm; F–G, J = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885284/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
). Inner paleae cylindrical, finely tapering, with conspicuous thecae partially surrounding subdistal margins and slightly curved, smooth tip (
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,445,1784]" captionTargetId="figure-77@8.[192,1396,445,1784]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Mariansabellaria caribbea sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-303). A. Outer palea dorsal. B. Basal region of dorsal outer palea. C. Middle region of dorsal outer palea. D. Details of the outer palea tip. E. Basal region of ventral outer palea. F. Dorsal inner palea. G. Ventral inner palea. H. Details of the inner palea tip.I. Parathoracic chaeta. J–K. Abdominal chaetae.L. Abdominal uncini. Numbers indicate the rows of teeth. Scale bars: A = 200 µm; B, D, H–I, K = 20 µm; C, L = 10 µm; E = 50 µm; F–G, J = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885284/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Fig. 4F– H</figureCitation>
). Opercular stalk light brown, twice as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[874,971,335,361]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1852,1878]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,472,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-45@7.[189,1398,472,1815]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Mariansabellaria caribbea sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-303). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view.B. Anterior region left lateral view.C. Anterior region ventral view.D. Nuchal spines.E. Parathorax left lateral view. F. Caudal peduncle. Abbreviations: bo = building organ; c1 = cirrus 1st thoracic; c2 = cirri 2nd thoracic segment; ne = parathoracic neuropodium; no = parathoracic notopodium. Numbers indicate the tentacular filaments. Scale bars: A–B, E: 1 mm; C, F: 0.5 mm; D: 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885282" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885282/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Seven opercular papillae on right lobe, three papillae on left; fragile, easily detachable tissue. Three pairs of tentacles, simple, grooved (
<figureCitation box="[200,294,406,432]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1852,1878]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,472,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-45@7.[189,1398,472,1815]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Mariansabellaria caribbea sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-303). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view.B. Anterior region left lateral view.C. Anterior region ventral view.D. Nuchal spines.E. Parathorax left lateral view. F. Caudal peduncle. Abbreviations: bo = building organ; c1 = cirrus 1st thoracic; c2 = cirri 2nd thoracic segment; ne = parathoracic neuropodium; no = parathoracic notopodium. Numbers indicate the tentacular filaments. Scale bars: A–B, E: 1 mm; C, F: 0.5 mm; D: 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885282" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885282/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
). Nuchal spines cylindrical, embedded in opercular tissue; two on left lobe and three in right one (
<figureCitation box="[249,343,441,467]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1852,1878]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,472,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-45@7.[189,1398,472,1815]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Mariansabellaria caribbea sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-303). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view.B. Anterior region left lateral view.C. Anterior region ventral view.D. Nuchal spines.E. Parathorax left lateral view. F. Caudal peduncle. Abbreviations: bo = building organ; c1 = cirrus 1st thoracic; c2 = cirri 2nd thoracic segment; ne = parathoracic neuropodium; no = parathoracic notopodium. Numbers indicate the tentacular filaments. Scale bars: A–B, E: 1 mm; C, F: 0.5 mm; D: 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885282" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885282/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
). Median ridge short, with some marginal eyespots. Median organ absent.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885284" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6885284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885284/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="117" startId="8.[189,232,1822,1848]" targetBox="[192,1396,445,1784]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph blockId="8.[188,1399,1822,2025]" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,268,1822,1848]" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">Fig. 4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Chávez-López, 2022" authorityName="Chávez-López" authorityYear="2022" box="[277,596,1822,1848]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="8" pageNumber="117" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="caribbea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[277,596,1822,1848]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">Mariansabellaria caribbea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[605,699,1823,1849]" pageId="8" pageNumber="117" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype (ECOSUR-303). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1028,1049,1822,1848]" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">A</emphasis>
. Outer palea dorsal. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1299,1317,1822,1848]" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">B</emphasis>
. Basal region of dorsal outer palea. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[536,555,1857,1883]" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">C</emphasis>
. Middle region of dorsal outer palea. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1014,1033,1857,1883]" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">D</emphasis>
. Details of the outer palea tip. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[191,209,1893,1919]" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">E</emphasis>
. Basal region of ventral outer palea. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[654,671,1893,1919]" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">F</emphasis>
. Dorsal inner palea. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[921,942,1892,1918]" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">G</emphasis>
. Ventral inner palea. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1200,1221,1893,1919]" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">H</emphasis>
. Details of the inner palea tip. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[366,377,1928,1954]" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">I</emphasis>
. Parathoracic chaeta. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[632,683,1928,1954]" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">J–K</emphasis>
. Abdominal chaetae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[933,953,1928,1954]" pageId="8" pageNumber="117">L</emphasis>
. Abdominal uncini. Numbers indicate the rows of teeth. Scale bars: A = 200 µm; B, D, H–I, K = 20 µm; C, L = 10 µm; E = 50 µm; F–G, J = 100 µm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,1399,506,568]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">
THORAX. First thoracic segment with long, triangular-shaped lateral lobe and capillary neurochaetae. Second chaetiger with short, triangular-shaped lateral lobe, without chaetae (
<figureCitation box="[1089,1180,542,568]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1852,1878]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,472,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-45@7.[189,1398,472,1815]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Mariansabellaria caribbea sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-303). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view.B. Anterior region left lateral view.C. Anterior region ventral view.D. Nuchal spines.E. Parathorax left lateral view. F. Caudal peduncle. Abbreviations: bo = building organ; c1 = cirrus 1st thoracic; c2 = cirri 2nd thoracic segment; ne = parathoracic neuropodium; no = parathoracic notopodium. Numbers indicate the tentacular filaments. Scale bars: A–B, E: 1 mm; C, F: 0.5 mm; D: 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885282" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885282/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[188,1398,607,704]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">
PARATHORAX. With four segments, body wall eroded, branchiae translucent, fragile (
<figureCitation box="[1162,1253,607,633]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1852,1878]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,472,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-45@7.[189,1398,472,1815]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Mariansabellaria caribbea sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-303). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view.B. Anterior region left lateral view.C. Anterior region ventral view.D. Nuchal spines.E. Parathorax left lateral view. F. Caudal peduncle. Abbreviations: bo = building organ; c1 = cirrus 1st thoracic; c2 = cirri 2nd thoracic segment; ne = parathoracic neuropodium; no = parathoracic notopodium. Numbers indicate the tentacular filaments. Scale bars: A–B, E: 1 mm; C, F: 0.5 mm; D: 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885282" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885282/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
). Pigmented tissue, in dorsal view, with seven reddish transverse lines (
<figureCitation box="[906,1003,642,668]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1852,1878]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,472,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-45@7.[189,1398,472,1815]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Mariansabellaria caribbea sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-303). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view.B. Anterior region left lateral view.C. Anterior region ventral view.D. Nuchal spines.E. Parathorax left lateral view. F. Caudal peduncle. Abbreviations: bo = building organ; c1 = cirrus 1st thoracic; c2 = cirri 2nd thoracic segment; ne = parathoracic neuropodium; no = parathoracic notopodium. Numbers indicate the tentacular filaments. Scale bars: A–B, E: 1 mm; C, F: 0.5 mm; D: 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885282" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885282/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Notopodia with lanceolate and capillary chaetae (
<figureCitation box="[403,486,677,704]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,445,1784]" captionTargetId="figure-77@8.[192,1396,445,1784]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Mariansabellaria caribbea sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-303). A. Outer palea dorsal. B. Basal region of dorsal outer palea. C. Middle region of dorsal outer palea. D. Details of the outer palea tip. E. Basal region of ventral outer palea. F. Dorsal inner palea. G. Ventral inner palea. H. Details of the inner palea tip.I. Parathoracic chaeta. J–K. Abdominal chaetae.L. Abdominal uncini. Numbers indicate the rows of teeth. Scale bars: A = 200 µm; B, D, H–I, K = 20 µm; C, L = 10 µm; E = 50 µm; F–G, J = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885284/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Fig. 4I</figureCitation>
). Neuropodia with only capillary chaetae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,1400,743,875]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">
ABDOMEN. Abdominal region bent, body wall damaged, branchiae translucent, fragile, present only in first four segments. Abdominal segments colorless. Neurochaetae capillary, ornamented with irregular thecal laminar extensions (
<figureCitation box="[511,635,813,839]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,445,1784]" captionTargetId="figure-77@8.[192,1396,445,1784]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Mariansabellaria caribbea sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-303). A. Outer palea dorsal. B. Basal region of dorsal outer palea. C. Middle region of dorsal outer palea. D. Details of the outer palea tip. E. Basal region of ventral outer palea. F. Dorsal inner palea. G. Ventral inner palea. H. Details of the inner palea tip.I. Parathoracic chaeta. J–K. Abdominal chaetae.L. Abdominal uncini. Numbers indicate the rows of teeth. Scale bars: A = 200 µm; B, D, H–I, K = 20 µm; C, L = 10 µm; E = 50 µm; F–G, J = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885284/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Fig. 4J–K</figureCitation>
). Notopodia with series of uncini with 9–10 transverse rows of teeth (
<figureCitation box="[262,354,848,875]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,445,1784]" captionTargetId="figure-77@8.[192,1396,445,1784]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Mariansabellaria caribbea sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-303). A. Outer palea dorsal. B. Basal region of dorsal outer palea. C. Middle region of dorsal outer palea. D. Details of the outer palea tip. E. Basal region of ventral outer palea. F. Dorsal inner palea. G. Ventral inner palea. H. Details of the inner palea tip.I. Parathoracic chaeta. J–K. Abdominal chaetae.L. Abdominal uncini. Numbers indicate the rows of teeth. Scale bars: A = 200 µm; B, D, H–I, K = 20 µm; C, L = 10 µm; E = 50 µm; F–G, J = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885284/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Fig. 4L</figureCitation>
). Caudal peduncle whitish, slightly annulate (
<figureCitation box="[889,979,848,875]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1852,1878]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,472,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-45@7.[189,1398,472,1815]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Mariansabellaria caribbea sp. nov., holotype (ECOSUR-303). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view.B. Anterior region left lateral view.C. Anterior region ventral view.D. Nuchal spines.E. Parathorax left lateral view. F. Caudal peduncle. Abbreviations: bo = building organ; c1 = cirrus 1st thoracic; c2 = cirri 2nd thoracic segment; ne = parathoracic neuropodium; no = parathoracic notopodium. Numbers indicate the tentacular filaments. Scale bars: A–B, E: 1 mm; C, F: 0.5 mm; D: 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885282" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885282/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="118" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,303,914,940]" box="[189,303,914,940]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,914,940]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,914,940]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,1399,960,1128]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">
<taxonomicName authority="Chávez-López, 2022" authorityName="Chávez-López" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,506,960,986]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="caribbea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,506,960,986]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Mariansabellaria caribbea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[515,606,961,987]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
shares the presence of transverse margins on the inner paleae with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirtley" authorityYear="1994" box="[191,316,996,1022]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="chilena">
<emphasis box="[191,316,996,1022]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">M. chilena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirtley" authorityYear="1994" box="[333,472,996,1022]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tenhovei">
<emphasis box="[333,472,996,1022]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">M. tenhovei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stromgren" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[541,698,996,1021]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="norvegica">
<emphasis box="[541,698,996,1021]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">M. norvegica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the outer paleae with thecae that do not surround the blade, also called ‘hemithecae’ by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kirtley D. W." box="[593,760,1031,1057]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" refId="ref15203" refString="Kirtley D. W. 1994. A Review and Taxonomic Revision of the Family Sabellariidae Johnston, 1865 (Annelida: Polychaeta). Sabecon Press Science Series, Stuart, Florida." type="book" year="1994">Kirtley (1994)</bibRefCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirtley" authorityYear="1994" box="[811,935,1031,1057]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="chilena">
<emphasis box="[811,935,1031,1057]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">M. chilena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirtley" authorityYear="1994" box="[1071,1209,1031,1057]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tenhovei">
<emphasis box="[1071,1209,1031,1057]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">M. tenhovei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirtley" authorityYear="1994" box="[1224,1348,1031,1057]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="chilena">
<emphasis box="[1224,1348,1031,1057]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">M. chilena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Chávez-López, 2022" authorityName="Chávez-López" authorityYear="2022" box="[190,332,1066,1092]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="caribbea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[190,332,1066,1092]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">M. caribbea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[339,429,1067,1093]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differ in the number of buccal tentacles. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kirtley D. W." box="[908,1075,1066,1092]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" refId="ref15203" refString="Kirtley D. W. 1994. A Review and Taxonomic Revision of the Family Sabellariidae Johnston, 1865 (Annelida: Polychaeta). Sabecon Press Science Series, Stuart, Florida." type="book" year="1994">Kirtley (1994)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirtley" authorityYear="1994" box="[1202,1339,1066,1092]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tenhovei">
<emphasis box="[1202,1339,1066,1092]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">M. tenhovei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with five pairs of buccal tentacles and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirtley" authorityYear="1994" box="[566,688,1101,1127]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="chilena">
<emphasis box="[566,688,1101,1127]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">M. chilena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with six pairs, while 
<taxonomicName authority="Chávez-López, 2022" authorityName="Chávez-López" authorityYear="2022" box="[929,1069,1101,1127]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="caribbea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[929,1069,1101,1127]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">M. caribbea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1076,1165,1102,1128]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
only has three pairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[187,1399,1166,1369]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">
<taxonomicName authority="Chávez-López, 2022" authorityName="Chávez-López" authorityYear="2022" box="[187,508,1167,1193]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="caribbea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[187,508,1167,1193]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Mariansabellaria caribbea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[516,608,1167,1193]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is characterized by having more than 50 pairs of outer paleae with irregularly expanded margins resembling small denticles, 4–5 inner paleae, and only three pairs of buccal tentacles. Although the outer paleae of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stromgren" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[756,916,1238,1263]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="norvegica">
<emphasis box="[756,916,1238,1263]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">M. norvegica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also have irregular margins resembling denticles, 
<bibRefCitation author="Stromgren T." box="[308,517,1272,1298]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref15284" refString="Stromgren T. 1971. A new species of Phalacrostemma (Annelida Polychaeta: Sabellariidae) from the Norwegian west coast. Kongelige Norske videnskabers selskabs skrifter 14: 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1971">Strömgren (1971)</bibRefCitation>
did not describe the number of opercular paleae. However, the two species differ in the morphology of the thecae of the outer paleae, and in the number of teeth on the abdominal uncini, seven pairs in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stromgren" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[446,602,1343,1368]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="norvegica">
<emphasis box="[446,602,1343,1368]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">M. norvegica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 9–10 pairs in 
<taxonomicName authority="Chávez-López, 2022" authorityName="Chávez-López" authorityYear="2022" box="[819,963,1343,1369]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="caribbea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[819,963,1343,1369]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">M. caribbea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[970,1060,1343,1369]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[188,1398,1408,1540]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">
<bibRefCitation author="Kirtley D. W." box="[189,357,1408,1434]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" refId="ref15203" refString="Kirtley D. W. 1994. A Review and Taxonomic Revision of the Family Sabellariidae Johnston, 1865 (Annelida: Polychaeta). Sabecon Press Science Series, Stuart, Florida." type="book" year="1994">Kirtley (1994)</bibRefCitation>
only provided the number of opercular paleae for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirtley" authorityYear="1994" box="[945,1083,1408,1434]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="harrisae">
<emphasis box="[945,1083,1408,1434]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">M. harrisae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with 24 pairs of outer and 10 pairs of inner paleae. In addition to the difference in the number of opercular paleae, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirtley" authorityYear="1994" box="[1214,1352,1443,1469]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="harrisae">
<emphasis box="[1214,1352,1443,1469]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">M. harrisae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has smooth inner paleae and five buccal tentacles per lobe, while 
<taxonomicName authority="Chávez-López, 2022" authorityName="Chávez-López" authorityYear="2022" box="[905,1048,1478,1504]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="caribbea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[905,1048,1478,1504]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">M. caribbea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1055,1145,1479,1505]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has inner paleae with conspicuous thecae and three tentacles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="118" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,342,1579,1605]" box="[189,342,1579,1605]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,342,1579,1605]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,342,1579,1605]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,1398,1626,1687]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">
Banco Chinchorro, 
<collectingRegion box="[418,584,1626,1652]" country="Mexico" name="Quintana Roo" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Quintana Roo</collectingRegion>
, at 
<quantity box="[623,697,1626,1652]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7399999999999998" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" unit="m" value="274.0">274 m</quantity>
depth. This is the first record of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirtley" authorityYear="1994" box="[1191,1398,1626,1652]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Mariansabellaria" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1191,1398,1626,1652]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Mariansabellaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the western Atlantic (
<figureCitation box="[470,558,1661,1687]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="37.[189,232,1795,1821]" captionTargetBox="[203,1386,282,1742]" captionTargetId="figure-12@37.[189,1398,265,1758]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="Fig. 22. Localities for studied specimens. A. Caribbean Sea and the Gulf of Mexico. B. South Florida. C. Southeastern Bahamas. The crosses indicate type localities of species previously recorded in the tropical Western Atlantic." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885320" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885320/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
